<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-16-0720 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Itaipu hydroelectric power plant with its total capacity of 12 600megawatts is the largest power plant of the world. One of the main pillarsof operational safety and reliability is the electrical protection systemof the plant that must be carefully planned and tested during the commissioningphase. The article reviews the work performed and the operating experienceso far that confirmed the faultless functioning of the electrostaticunit protection system.</TEXT></DOC>